## 7. Skills & team

A POC of this kind typically needs the following roles (some can be combined on a small team):

- **Domain SME — Maintenance Supervisor / auditor.** Defines what "normal" and "problematic" mean, and labels the golden dataset. Without this, the system has no ground truth.
- **Data engineer.** S3/Glue/Lambda pipelines, data cleaning, joining job/vehicle/part/labour/technician records, handling messy real-world data.
- **ML / data scientist.** Builds the statistical baselines and outlier scoring in SageMaker; defines anomaly thresholds.
- **GenAI / agent engineer.** Designs the agent pipeline (Bedrock Agents / Strands), prompt engineering, retrieval design, guardrails.
- **Cloud / MLOps engineer.** Step Functions orchestration, deployment, scaling, cost control, monitoring, IAM/security.
- **Evaluation / QA lead.** Designs the golden dataset and the metrics; runs the evaluation harness; tracks precision/recall.
- **Product owner / project lead.** Owns scope, success criteria, stakeholder alignment (supervisors, internal reviewers, fleet managers, leadership), and the rollout plan.
- **Frontend engineer (part-time).** Builds the reviewer feed/UI.

Underlying skills: Python and boto3; AWS solution architecture; embeddings/RAG; agent design and prompt engineering; classical ML and anomaly detection; data modelling (and graph modelling for the later phases); and evaluation methodology for AI systems.

